{"word":"γαυριάω","slug":"γαυριάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>γαυριάω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <a href='S:γαυρόομαι'><el>γαυρόομαι</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>mostly in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> and <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>mid.</a>\n<p/><i>to bear oneself proudly, prance</i>, of horses, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b>; and in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:—<a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to pride oneself</i> on a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>; <el>ἐπί σφισι</el> <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/>"}]}